{"id":4346,"date":"2022-05-25T11:47:43","date_gmt":"2022-05-25T08:47:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/?p=4346"},"modified":"2022-05-25T11:47:43","modified_gmt":"2022-05-25T08:47:43","slug":"monero-price-prediction-2022-and-beyond-will-xmr-reach-1000","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/monero-price-prediction-2022-and-beyond-will-xmr-reach-1000\/","title":{"rendered":"Monero Price Prediction 2022 and Beyond &#8211; Will XMR Reach $1000"},"content":{"rendered":"<p> <br \/>\n<\/p>\n<div>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero was launched in 2014 with the simple goal of letting the transactions occur with <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/www.getmonero.org\/\">privacy and anonymity<\/a>. As a private and decentralized <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/top-9-cryptocurrencies-in-2022\/\">cryptocurrency<\/a>, it keeps its investor\u2019s assets secure and confidential. With the transparency of systems in some other assets that claim to conceal a person\u2019s identity, it becomes easy to trace the original source of payments. This is because cryptocurrency usage is monitored on them. However, XMR solves this by obscuring senders and the recipients in the same way as using advanced cryptography.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With the use of various privacy-enhancing technologies for anonymity, the makers of Monero have said that their first priority is privacy and security, along with easy usability and then efficiency. Protection is the same for all users, irrespective of their technological competence. They aim to enable fast and affordable payments without any risk of censorship.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero (XMR) Fundamental Analysis<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero is the leading cryptocurrency known for its private and censorship-resistant transactions. Stealth Addresses, Ring Signatures, and RingCT are the technologies that hide the identity of the sender, receiver, and the number of transactions. They are unlinked to real-world identities and hence are untraceable. It is a truly fungible currency that ends the merchant\u2019s worry of getting tainted or blocked. Being an electrical asset, its fast and inexpensive transactions can take place anywhere in the world, as there is no need for check clearing fees, wire transfers, multiple-day holding periods, and fake chargebacks. It is also free of any legal jurisdictions and formalities and safe from capital control due to real decentralization.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero\u2019s grassroots community appeals to the best researchers and engineers related to cryptocurrencies. The project is the representation of the privacy and security of cryptocurrency as its development team, and research labs are continuously working to achieve them both. About five hundred developers have contributed to its betterment from all over the world from the time of its launch. Various platforms and chatrooms are available for joining and working as the community is always welcomed by them.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How Monero Works<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are many features that make Monero unique, and its decentralization is among the best among them, as users don\u2019t need to trust anyone on the platform. Monero tries its best to keep itself decentralized using a consensus mechanism based on a <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/what-is-proof-of-work\/\">proof-of-work<\/a> mechanism called CryptoNight. It prevents the domination of large mining farms. Although it was formed on the fork of Bytecoin, it gets advanced through its CryptoNote technology. The Ring Confidential Transactions (RingCT), created in 2015, needs a multi-layered and anonymous group signature that very efficiently enables hidden amounts and the arrival or destination of the transaction.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero also utilizes a stealth address to add more security to the user\u2019s privacy. This technology randomly forms one-time addresses. It ensures that the transactions are not linked to each other in any way. Recipients use this to get payments to shield their unmatched address on the <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/what-is-blockchain\/\">blockchain<\/a>. In the presence of this technology, whenever a sender sends XMR, the payments received are then moved to the unique public address, with the assurance that a user\u2019s wallet address would never be published on the blockchain.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Traceability becomes impossible for the <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/cryptocurrency-wallet-definition\/\">wallet<\/a> addresses, transactions between users, and features within the XMR token itself, as fungibility is one of the features of Monero. With fungibility, XMR is quite similar to cash; just as if you borrow a dollar one day, you will get a differently valued dollar the next day. This is what fungibility refers to. It makes these assets exchangeable and undifferentiated from the same class of other assets. Although other cryptocurrencies like bitcoin are also considered fungible tokens, XMR makes all the tokens equally undifferentiated by obscuring its transaction history of itself.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Other than that, ring signatures technology is used for achieving obfuscation. Past outputs in transactions are picked up from the blockchain and act as decoys, making it impossible for outside observers to identify the one who has signed it. The amount sent by a person to another can be split into several random chunks to make this even more difficult. These distinctive features have made XMR a very unauthorized medium for transactions, particularly for the darknet markets, and governments of various countries have offered millions of dollars to anyone who is capable of cracking their code.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tokenomics<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Monero network has a native currency, which is XMR. XMR is used as the tool for peer-to-peer payments, acts as fees for transactions, and serves as the storage of value for the Monero network. Monero is also used to pay fees for transactions. Through their extraordinary privacy features, they automatically get anonymity and have received extensive usage as a grey and black-market currency. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero was created by a group of seven developers, with no pre-mine and instant-mine, in 2014, right after the forking of Bytecoin\u2019s codebase with a controversial 80% pre-mine. It implements a regularly decreasing block reward, and when it reached 0.6 XMR in each block in 2022, the block reward no longer decreases. In every future block, 0.6 new XMR gets created. This tail emission regularly has its effect on providing Monero with a low and visually decreasing rate of annual supply issuance to the extent it becomes negligible.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero Future Plans<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Before talking about the future plans of Monero, we can see the past accomplishments from their old roadmaps. In 2014, they launched Bitcointalk and changed Bitmonero\u2019s name to Monero. They also published three research lab papers in 2014 and one in 2015. The release of Hydrogen Helix, Wolfram Warptangent, official GUI Beta 1, a network update, and another research lab paper took place in 2016. In 2017, they enabled RingCT transactions through a network upgrade and minimized block size and dynamic fee algorithm. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The website was redesigned with the release of another research paper. Lithium Luna and the new proof-of-work Cryptonight v2 mechanism were released in 2018. In 2019, the website got localized in German and released the Boron butterfly. In 2020, the website was translatable on Weblate, and the Dandelion++ protocol got implemented. In 2021, an onion address got generated for Monero\u2019s official platform, and the P2 pool was released.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the future, they are planning to launch Haveno. Haveno is going to be built on Tor and Monero and is a non-custodial decentralized exchange for crypto and fiat currencies. They also want to launch more bulletproofs that are short, un-interactive, no knowledge proofs with no need of a trusted setup. Other plans are return addresses, second-layer solutions for higher speed and scalability, and triptych, which were logarithmic-sized linkable ring signatures with applications.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monero (XMR) Price Analysis<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Monero price is $193 currently, with a trading volume of about $205 million. The CoinMarketCap ranks it currently at #25. Now it has a market cap of approximately $3.5 billion, with a circulating <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/what-is-circulating-supply-and-maximum-supply\/\">supply<\/a> of 18 million XMR coins. It has a very good record in terms of price.<\/span><\/p>\n<div class=\"cryptoboxes\" id=\"mcw-26647\" data-realtime=\"on\">\n<div class=\"mcw-box mcw-box-6 mcw-white-theme mcw-rounded\">\n<div class=\"mcw-box-row\">\n<div class=\"mcw-box-content\">\n<div class=\"mcw-box-column\"><span class=\"coin-img\"><img alt=\"monero\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\" http:=\"\" height=\"50\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgt